{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"221cedd7-9e4d-4cf2-a148-caf417c01246","content":"`.testsettings` files are **not supported** by modern MSTest (v3+). You need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Here's what I did:\n\n### Created `local.runsettings` mapping your three settings:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `AssemblyResolution` / `useLoadContext` | `<DeploymentEnabled>true</DeploymentEnabled>` in `<MSTest>` |\n| `TestTimeout` = 30000 | `<TestSessionTimeout>30000</TestSessionTimeout>` in `<RunConfiguration>` |\n| Code Coverage data collector | `<DataCollector>` with updated v2.0 URI |\n\n### Updated `.csproj` to reference it:\nAdded `<RunSettingsFilePath>` so the settings are picked up automatically.\n\nYou can now **delete `local.testsettings`** — it has no effect with MSTest 3.x. If you also want a **per-test** timeout (not session-wide), add `[Timeout(30000)]` to test methods or set `<TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>` inside `<MSTest>`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cfbd3828-7e13-4ff0-8677-62779aee2020","outputTokens":288,"requestId":"5C2A:2582EE:4232AE:53166C:69F5618F"},"id":"cb62e613-dba1-4ae5-b44f-b2901625c8d4","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:29:42.065Z","parentId":"77d0754a-7761-4322-a98b-8b51179b7f8e"}
